  "text": "Surgical-site infection causes significant reduction in quality of life of patients and places enormous burdens on healthcare systems. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In orthopaedic surgical-site infections this translates to a greater than 300% increase in healthcare costs, increased hospital stays, re-admissions and poor patient outcomes. [CITATION_3] Pneumatic tourniquets are routinely employed in orthopaedic surgery. Most institutions do not have a standard protocol for cleaning tourniquets. [CITATION_4] Non-sterile tourniquets which are used repetitively on patients without a standard protocol for their cleaning may be a source of infection.",
